   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# User Activation Funnel Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes onboarding and activation events to understand what user actions correlate with successful activation and where new users struggle most.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Define and measure \\\"activation\\\" from event data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Build an activation funnel with step-wise conversion rates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify activation-correlated actions and user segments.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Recommend onboarding improvements based on data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Many users sign up but never reach the \\\"aha moment.\\\" Identifying what distinguishes activated users from those who churn early is critical for product growth.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Activation is the strongest leading indicator of long-term retention. Improving activation rate by 10% typically improves 6-month retention by 5-7%.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **4,000 new users** tracked through onboarding actions over their first 7 days.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 4000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ACTIVATION_ACTIONS = [\\\"complete_profile\\\", \\\"first_project\\\", \\\"invite_member\\\", \\\"first_export\\\", \\\"connect_integration\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SOURCES = [\\\"Organic\\\", \\\"Paid\\\", \\\"Referral\\\", \\\"Product Hunt\\\", \\\"Social\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PLANS = [\\\"Free\\\", \\\"Trial\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    source = rng.choice(SOURCES, p=[0.30, 0.25, 0.20, 0.10, 0.15])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plan = rng.choice(PLANS, p=[0.60, 0.40])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Trial users are more motivated\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    base_prob = 0.65 if plan == \\\"Trial\\\" else 0.45\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    actions = {}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for action in ACTIVATION_ACTIONS:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        prob = base_prob * (0.9 if action in [\\\"complete_profile\\\", \\\"first_project\\\"] else 0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        if source == \\\"Referral\\\":\\n\",\n",
    "    \"            prob *= 1.1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        actions[action] = int(rng.random() < np.clip(prob, 0.1, 0.9))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        base_prob *= 0.85  # Each subsequent action is less likely\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    actions_done = sum(actions.values())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    activated = 1 if actions_done >= 3 else 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    day7_logins = max(0, int(rng.normal(3 + actions_done * 1.5, 2)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    day30_active = int(rng.random() < (0.7 if activated else 0.15))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    row = {\\\"user_id\\\": f\\\"U{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"source\\\": source, \\\"plan\\\": plan,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"           \\\"actions_completed\\\": actions_done, \\\"activated\\\": activated,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"           \\\"day7_logins\\\": day7_logins, \\\"day30_active\\\": day30_active}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    row.update(actions)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append(row)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}, Activation rate: {df['activated'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Activation Funnel\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"action_rates = df[ACTIVATION_ACTIONS].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"action_rates.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Action Completion Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_xlabel(\\\"% of Users\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Activated vs not by source\\n\",\n",
    "    \"act_by_source = df.groupby(\\\"source\\\")[\\\"activated\\\"].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"act_by_source.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Activation Rate by Source\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Correlation of each action with activation and 30-day retention\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for target in [\\\"activated\\\", \\\"day30_active\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    corrs = df[ACTIVATION_ACTIONS + [target]].corr()[target].drop(target).sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\nCorrelation with {target}:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(corrs.round(3))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# 30-day retention by activation status\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ret_by_act = df.groupby(\\\"activated\\\")[\\\"day30_active\\\"].mean()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ret_by_act.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=ax, color=[\\\"#e74c3c\\\", \\\"#2ecc71\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"30-Day Retention by Activation Status\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"30-Day Active Rate\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xticklabels([\\\"Not Activated\\\", \\\"Activated\\\"], rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Activated 30-day retention: {ret_by_act[1]:.1%}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Not activated 30-day retention: {ret_by_act[0]:.1%}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **\\\"first_project\\\" and \\\"complete_profile\\\" are the most completed actions** and the strongest activation predictors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Activated users have dramatically higher 30-day retention.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Trial plan users activate at higher rates** than Free users — motivation matters.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Referral users have the highest activation rate** — warm introductions drive engagement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **\\\"connect_integration\\\" is the least completed action** but correlates with strong retention.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real activation patterns are more complex.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Binary action tracking misses action depth.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No session-level or feature-level engagement data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Make \\\"first_project\\\" the primary onboarding goal — it's the strongest activation signal.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Reduce friction for integration connection — guided setup could lift adoption.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Implement in-app onboarding checklist to gamify action completion.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. A/B test different activation definitions (3 actions vs 2 actions threshold).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Defining activation as just \\\"logged in\\\" — it must involve value-generating actions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Measuring activation without a time window (must be within first 7 days, etc.).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Not connecting activation to downstream retention.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Optimizing for action count instead of specific high-value actions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Test different activation thresholds (2, 3, 4 actions) and compare 30-day retention.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Build a decision tree to predict activation from user attributes.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Create a \\\"time to activate\\\" metric and analyze what affects it.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Design an A/B test for a new onboarding flow.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Activation is the strongest predictor of long-term retention.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Completing a first project is the most important onboarding action.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Source quality matters** — referral users activate best.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Focus onboarding optimization on the 3 actions most correlated with 30-day retention.**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
